# github-bot environment variables
# ---------------------------------
# Copy to .env and fill in real values. .env is gitignored.
#
# Retrieve CLIPROXY_API_KEY from the homelab LXC 100:
#   ssh root@192.168.50.114 \
#     "python3 -c 'import yaml; print(yaml.safe_load(open(\"/opt/cli-proxy-api/config.yaml\"))[\"api-keys\"][0])'"

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# CLIProxyAPI (homelab LLM backend)
# Upstream: https://github.com/router-for-me/CLIProxyAPI
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
CLIPROXY_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# pr-agent uses OPENAI_KEY for LiteLLM auth regardless of the underlying provider
OPENAI_KEY=${CLIPROXY_API_KEY}

# NOTE: Model (CONFIG.MODEL) and endpoint (OPENAI.API_BASE) are already pinned
# in .pr_agent.toml and pr_agent/settings/configuration.toml. You only need
# OPENAI_KEY to run this locally.
#
# If you want to override them, bash cannot export vars containing dots, so use:
#   export 'OPENAI.API_BASE=http://192.168.50.114:8317/v1'
#   export 'CONFIG.MODEL=kimi-k2.6'
# Or use python-dotenv / direnv style loaders that handle quoted keys.
#
# Available models (24 total) — see .pr_agent.toml or `curl ../v1/models`:
#   Kimi:                  kimi-k2.6, kimi-k2.5
#   Codex (GPT):           openai/gpt-5.2, openai/gpt-5.1, openai/gpt-5, gpt-5-codex-mini,
#                          gpt-5.1-codex-max, gpt-4.1, gpt-4.1-mini
#   Antigravity (Gemini):  gemini-3-pro-preview, gemini-3-flash-preview, gemini-2.5-flash
#   Antigravity (Claude):  claude-sonnet-4-6, ag-claude-sonnet-4-5, ag-claude-sonnet-4-5-thinking

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub (only needed for local CLI runs; Actions handles this automatically)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub App (required for GitHub App mode deployment)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# GITHUB_APP_ID=3540327
# GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-webhook-secret
#
# GITHUB_PRIVATE_KEY: GitHub App's private key in PEM format.
#   1. Go to GitHub App settings → Private keys → Generate a private key
#   2. Download the .pem file
#   3. Convert to single-line format (replace newlines with \n):
#      awk 'NF {sub(/\r/, ""); printf "%s\\n", $0}' github-app.pem
#   4. Paste the output below (include BEGIN/END lines):
# GITHUB_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----"

